content:
Pandora Hearts Review ♥
Plot :: There is something really special about this. Although the plot includes elements and themes from other works, like Alice In Wonderland,  it also has it's own originality added into the mix that gives it a spark! Many elements are deprived from the Victorian era, gothic, and a dark fantasy feel.  I truly enjoyed the story presented in Pandora Hearts. However, a lot of details aren't given away to you upfront and sometimes you will become utterly confused about certain situations. There are many plot twists.  But I love how it keeps you guessing. The story feels like it was reallywell thought out. The plot twists don't feel forced or rushed. The only negatives I have with it is the pacing can be a bit slow and explanations are usually vague, only to be explained much later. Its hard to explain much about the plot since it becomes more complicated as you travel further. You would need to find out for yourself. Overall, I absolutely love the plot!! I give it a score of 9/10 {Great!} 


*Note* The story doesn't end at episode 22. The Manga series is ongoing, so if you want to find out what happens next, I would suggest reading the manga! :] The ending of the Anime doesn't give a clear solution and isn't complete.  The rest of the story is covered in the Manga and it reviles the mysteries in a creative matter!


Art :: For the most part, I think the artwork and style is beautiful. I love the character designs and drawing style used. As for animation, it certainly wasn't the most smooth or vivid. It appeared to have an old fashioned sort of look, which suits the anime's theme well. At times the animation is a bit choppy and inconsistent, but I wouldn't say it's awful.  At times the animation improves while other times it dips in quality. For some this may be bothersome, but I found I didn't have much of an issue with it. I give art an animation a score of 7/10 {Good} 


Sound :: The music consists of instrumentals that remind me of a theater presentation. The opening and ending  themes are beautiful and I like many of the background music in the show. At times though, music can be a bit too loud and drowned out voices. However, this doesn't happen to often, but I noticed it. Pandora Hearts has a nice soundtrack. (:  For voice acting, I would say is pretty good!! Sometimes the quality of the recordings can dip as well, but overall I don't have much complaints about sound! ^-^  The Anime is only done with Japanese dubs, so their is no English dubs available, just English subs. I give music and sound a score of 7/10 {Good} 


Characters :: I think the characters have something really special. They aren't completely generic or overly cliched. They present interesting personalities. I found myself enjoying many of the characters in the story. I give characters a score of 8/10 {Very Good!} 


Overall Enjoyment :: All in All, I love this Anime. I think the true heart of this series lies within the captivating story and variety of characters, these are the strongest points within Pandora Hearts and what I fell in love with.  This is why PH has become a favorite Anime of mine. I would recommend reading the Manga series as well. The story gets better and the twists are carried out beautifully. The artwork is also stunning!!
